          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683046823900-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the biryani is cooking, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong></p><p>Combine your<strong> mayo</strong> and <strong>remaining mint sauce</strong> in a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> – this is your <strong>minty mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1683046827667-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1683046827667-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1683046827667-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
